                    "description": "I was in Randstad Holding\u2019s HR team, where different the centers of expertise (TM, C&B and L&D) are responsible for HR strategy, programs and projects for Randstad's 38 Operating Companies (OpCos). As global HR analytics- and talent specialist I:\n\n- Was part of the \u2018global data management team\u2019. Goal was to increase data-driven decision making in the HR function, for which I started and/or managed projects to enrich our data landscape, improve data quality, and improve system adoption. \n- Analyzed and presented data insights and recommended actions related to talent management (i.e. female representation in sr. leadership, succession coverage, etc) and employee engagement (i.e. engagement trends during COVID, turnover analysis, etc). \n- Coordinated the data collection for Randstad's talent management process for sr. leadership (>2500 employees). \n- For the engagement tracker (>40,000 employees) I acted as a liaison for the OpCo's 38 engagement leads.\n- Governed data protection compliance in cooperation.\n\nAnd you can find some examples of the projects I worked on below:\n\n- Was responsible for the implementation of our HR analytics system (Crunchr) in 20 OpCos.\n- Led a project with an external consultant to perform a root-cause analysis identifying causes of, and solutions for, the dropping participation rates of Randstad\u2019s global engagement survey. \n- Was responsible for the addition of an EDI&B question set to our engagement survey. I covered the stakeholder management (HR directors & engagement leads of 38 OpCos), the training of 200 HR professionals, the organization of webinars for +-2000 managers, contract management and data protection compliance.\n- In cooperation with Randstad's EDI&B team I set up a pilot with four OpCos to collect data on diversity characteristics of employees (i.e. disability, gender identity, sexual orientation etc). Due to high complexity in close cooperation with experts from the legal, data protection and HR departments.",
